716 /******************************************************************************/

721 /* Analog to Digital Converter (ADC) */
722 /* */
723 /******************************************************************************/
724 /******************** Bits definition for ADC_ISR register ******************/
725 #define ADC_ISR_AWD ((uint32_t)0x00000080)
726 #define ADC_ISR_OVR ((uint32_t)0x00000010)
727 #define ADC_ISR_EOSEQ ((uint32_t)0x00000008)
728 #define ADC_ISR_EOC ((uint32_t)0x00000004)
729 #define ADC_ISR_EOSMP ((uint32_t)0x00000002)
730 #define ADC_ISR_ADRDY ((uint32_t)0x00000001)
732 /* Old EOSEQ bit definition, maintained for legacy purpose */
733 #define ADC_ISR_EOS ADC_ISR_EOSEQ
734 
735 /******************** Bits definition for ADC_IER register ******************/
736 #define ADC_IER_AWDIE ((uint32_t)0x00000080)
737 #define ADC_IER_OVRIE ((uint32_t)0x00000010)
738 #define ADC_IER_EOSEQIE ((uint32_t)0x00000008)
739 #define ADC_IER_EOCIE ((uint32_t)0x00000004)
740 #define ADC_IER_EOSMPIE ((uint32_t)0x00000002)
741 #define ADC_IER_ADRDYIE ((uint32_t)0x00000001)
743 /* Old EOSEQIE bit definition, maintained for legacy purpose */
744 #define ADC_IER_EOSIE ADC_IER_EOSEQIE
745 
746 /******************** Bits definition for ADC_CR register *******************/
747 #define ADC_CR_ADCAL ((uint32_t)0x80000000)
748 #define ADC_CR_ADSTP ((uint32_t)0x00000010)
749 #define ADC_CR_ADSTART ((uint32_t)0x00000004)
750 #define ADC_CR_ADDIS ((uint32_t)0x00000002)
751 #define ADC_CR_ADEN ((uint32_t)0x00000001)
753 /******************* Bits definition for ADC_CFGR1 register *****************/
754 #define ADC_CFGR1_AWDCH ((uint32_t)0x7C000000)
755 #define ADC_CFGR1_AWDCH_0 ((uint32_t)0x04000000)
756 #define ADC_CFGR1_AWDCH_1 ((uint32_t)0x08000000)
757 #define ADC_CFGR1_AWDCH_2 ((uint32_t)0x10000000)
758 #define ADC_CFGR1_AWDCH_3 ((uint32_t)0x20000000)
759 #define ADC_CFGR1_AWDCH_4 ((uint32_t)0x40000000)
760 #define ADC_CFGR1_AWDEN ((uint32_t)0x00800000)
761 #define ADC_CFGR1_AWDSGL ((uint32_t)0x00400000)
762 #define ADC_CFGR1_DISCEN ((uint32_t)0x00010000)
763 #define ADC_CFGR1_AUTOFF ((uint32_t)0x00008000)
764 #define ADC_CFGR1_WAIT ((uint32_t)0x00004000)
765 #define ADC_CFGR1_CONT ((uint32_t)0x00002000)
766 #define ADC_CFGR1_OVRMOD ((uint32_t)0x00001000)
767 #define ADC_CFGR1_EXTEN ((uint32_t)0x00000C00)

5267 /******************************************************************************/
5268 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F0xx device product */
5269 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
5270 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
5271 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
5272 /* product lines within the same STM32F0 Family */
5273 /******************************************************************************/
5274 
5275 /* Aliases for __IRQn */
5276 #define PVD_IRQn PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn
5277 #define VDDIO2_IRQn PVD_VDDIO2_IRQn
5278 #define RCC_IRQn RCC_CRS_IRQn
5279 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQn DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQn
5280 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQn ADC1_IRQn
5281 
5282 /* Aliases for __IRQHandler */
5283 #define PVD_IRQHandler PVD_VDDIO2_IRQHandler
5284 #define VDDIO2_IRQHandler PVD_VDDIO2_IRQHandler
5285 #define RCC_IRQHandler RCC_CRS_IRQHandler
5286 #define DMA1_Channel4_5_6_7_IRQHandler DMA1_Channel4_5_IRQHandler
5287 #define ADC1_COMP_IRQHandler ADC1_IRQHandler
5288 
5289 #ifdef __cplusplus
5290 }
5291 #endif /* __cplusplus */
5292 
5293 #endif /* __STM32F042x6_H */
